Merge pull request #23 from mozilla/trim-down-insecure-code; r=eoger

Trim down the `InsecureConnection` to a minimal implementation.

Trim down the `InsecureConnection` to a minimal implementation.

This exposes the same API as before, but uses no mock-TLS-like
infrastructure that might look more secure than it is.  The intention
is to help the subsequent actual-TLS PR land more cleanly.

Merge pull request #21 from mozilla/flat-jsm
Output a flat JSM file

Use EventTarget shim instead of the one in Window.

`window` in the Firefox privileged code context refers to the `hiddenDomWindow`.
On Windows and Linux, this window is loaded with a unpriviledged principal
instead of the all-powerfull system one. On these platforms and because of X-Ray
shenanigans we get errors when subclassing EventTarget.
Therefore we simply ship our own version of EventTarget.
